# 2. DISCOP
insert_opp '{"title":"DISCOP (Pan-African Content Market)","What Is It?":"DISCOP is a pan-African content market that connects content distributors and producers with acquisition and co-production executives through curated virtual and in-person meetings. Founded by Basic Lead, DISCOP has historically operated markets in Johannesburg and Abidjan (Ivory Coast), making it one of the longest-running dedicated African content trading platforms. The market focuses on content distribution — connecting sellers of finished content with African and international broadcasters, OTT platforms, and digital distributors. DISCOP also includes a co-production forum and training programmes. While the market has evolved from primarily in-person to include virtual components, it remains a significant platform for African content trading.","For Films or Series?":"All formats — television series, feature films, documentaries, formats, and digital content. Focus on finished content distribution and licensing.","What Do You Get If Selected?":"Pre-arranged one-to-one meetings with content buyers and distributors. Access to the co-production forum. Networking with African and international content professionals. Training programme access.","Cost":"Registration fee applies. Various delegate categories.","Next Deadline":"Check discop.com for upcoming market dates and registration.","Apply:":"discop.com","Who Can Apply / Eligibility":"Content distributors, producers, broadcasters, OTT platforms, and acquisition executives. Focus on African and international content professionals.","What to Submit":"Delegate registration via the DISCOP website. Content sellers should prepare screeners and sales materials.","Strongest Submission Tips":"DISCOP is particularly valuable for content that is ready for distribution — finished series, films, and formats seeking African broadcast partners. If you have completed content and want to reach African broadcasters and OTT platforms, DISCOP provides targeted matchmaking. Combined with MIP Africa (October, Cape Town) and the Durban FilmMart (July, Durban), DISCOP adds another touchpoint in the African content market calendar.","CALENDAR REMINDER:":"Check discop.com for upcoming market dates.","status":"approved","votes":0}'

