# 6. KOSINIMA Short Film Grant
insert_opp '{"title":"KOSINIMA SHORT FILM GRANT","What Is It?":"KOSINIMA, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit founded by Oluwaseun Babalola that provides films, grants, and career support for filmmakers in Africa and the African diaspora. The KOSINIMA Short Film Grant funds Black woman-identifying or non-binary filmmakers from Africa and the African diaspora (including Europe, the United States, the Caribbean, and South America) to produce short narrative or documentary films. The grant provides $2,500 USD per filmmaker for up to 4 filmmakers per cycle. Past grantees have produced work screened at international festivals. The grant operates on a periodic cycle — submissions open and close throughout the year.","For Films or Series?":"Short films only — narrative or documentary. Up to 4 filmmakers funded per cycle.","What Do You Get If Selected?":"$2,500 USD grant for short film production. Career support and mentorship from KOSINIMA network. Visibility through KOSINIMA'"'"'s platform and festival connections.","Cost":"FREE — No application fee","Next Deadline":"Submissions currently closed. Check kosinima.org/shortfilmgrant for the next open cycle.","Apply:":"kosinima.org/shortfilmgrant","Who Can Apply / Eligibility":"Black woman-identifying or non-binary filmmakers from Africa and the African diaspora (including Europe, United States, Caribbean, South America). Short narrative or documentary film projects.","What to Submit":"Project application as specified on the KOSINIMA website when submissions open.","Strongest Submission Tips":"KOSINIMA fills a critical niche — funding specifically for Black femme filmmakers from Africa and the diaspora. The $2,500 amount is modest but can fully fund a short film in many African contexts. A completed KOSINIMA-funded short can serve as a calling card for larger grants from Docubox, Africa No Filter, or the NFVF first-time filmmaker tier. Check back regularly as submission cycles open periodically.","CALENDAR REMINDER:":"Monitor kosinima.org/shortfilmgrant for next open submission cycle.","status":"approved","votes":0}'

