insert_opp '{"title":"UNESCO / TAMAYOUZ CINEMA FOUNDATION RESIDENCY (Morocco)","What Is It?":"The UNESCO/Tamayouz Cinema Foundation Residency is a fully supported creative residency for young African women filmmakers, held in Morocco. The programme provides mentorship, workshops, and a creative environment for participants to develop their film projects. It is part of UNESCO'"'"'s broader mandate to support cultural diversity and the creative industries in Africa. The residency is run in partnership with the Tamayouz Cinema Foundation, which focuses on empowering women in the African film industry. The programme covers accommodation, meals, and programme costs for selected participants.","For Films or Series?":"Film projects in development — fiction and documentary. Focus on emerging women filmmakers.","What Do You Get If Selected?":"Fully supported residency in Morocco. Mentorship from established filmmakers. Workshops on craft, production, and industry navigation. Time and space to develop your film project. Networking with fellow African women filmmakers.","Cost":"FREE — Fully supported (accommodation, meals, programme costs covered)","Next Deadline":"Periodic. Check UNESCO creativity portal and Tamayouz Cinema Foundation for upcoming calls.","Apply:":"unesco.org/creativity/en","Who Can Apply / Eligibility":"Young African women filmmakers. Emerging talent prioritised. Must have a film project in development.","What to Submit":"Application including project synopsis, director'"'"'s statement, CV, and work sample. Details published when call opens.","Strongest Submission Tips":"This residency is one of the few programmes specifically designed for young African women filmmakers. The Morocco location provides a creative environment at the crossroads of African, Arab, and European film cultures. Use the residency to develop your project to a stage where it is ready for submission to larger development labs (Realness, Locarno Open Doors, Sundance Labs) or funding (AFAC